    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1978-05-27T14:51:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1978-05-27T14:51:00-05:00" n="117"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d117">
                <head>117. Telegram From the Department of State to the Embassy in the Soviet
                        Union<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d117fn1">Source: National Archives,
                        RG 59, Central Foreign Policy File, P890106–1033. Secret; Immediate; <gloss
                            target="#t_NODIS_1">Nodis</gloss>. Drafted by McCall; cleared by
                            <persName corresp="#p_SHM_1">Shulman</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_LWH_1">Luers</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_TOM_1"
                            >Toon</persName>, Richard Castrodale (<gloss target="#t_SS_1"
                            >S/S</gloss>), and Victor Dikeos (<gloss target="#t_ASY_1"
                        >A/SY</gloss>); approved by <persName corresp="#p_CWM_1"
                            >Christopher</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1978-05-27T19:51:00+00:00">May 27, 1978, 1951Z</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>135977. Subject: Technical Penetration Protest. Ref: Moscow 11859.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d117fn2">Telegram 11859 from Moscow, May 26, is in the National
                        Archives, RG 59, Central Foreign Policy File, P890106–1035.</note>
                </p>
                <p>1. The Secretary May 26 orally protested penetration to <persName
                        corresp="#p_GAA_1">Gromyko</persName>,<note n="3" xml:id="d117fn3">No record
                        of the protest was found.</note> who said he had no information but would
                    look into the matter. We plan to hold off on a formal protest until you have
                    developed information on the scale of the penetration.</p>
                <p>2. Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_TOM_1">Toon</persName> concurs.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Vance</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
